    "problemStatement": "Sereja asks you to find out number of arrays **A** of size **N, i.e. A1, A2, ..., AN (1 ≤ Ai ≤ M)**, such that for each pair **i, j (1 ≤ i &lt; j ≤ N) gcd(Ai, Aj) = 1.** \n\n\n\nAs the answer could be large, print it modulo **109 + 7 (1000000007)**.",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **T** ≤ ** 10 **",
      "**1** ≤ **N** ≤ ** 105 **",
      "**1** ≤ **M** ≤ ** 100 **",
      "Subtasks",
      "Subtask #1: (10 points, TL = 5 secs) **1** ≤ **N, M** ≤ ** 10 **",
      "Subtask #2: (25 points, TL = 5 secs) **1** ≤ **N** ≤ ** 100 **",
      "Subtask #3: (65 points, TL = 5 secs) **original**",
      "Example**Input:**",
      "2",
      "1 1",
      "3 3",
      "**Output:**",
      "1",
      "13"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "First line of the input contain an integer **T** - number of test cases. \n\n\n**T** tests follow. First line of each test case contain two space separated integers **N, M**.",
    "outputFormat": "For each test case output required answer modulo **10^9 + 7**.",
